Chief Justice David Maraga has directed judicial officers to support President Uhuru Kenyatta in the fight against corruption. Maraga said as a judiciary, they will ensure zero tolerance to corruption by expediting cases involving the socio?economic vice.  Maraga said the public ought to get value for their monies in the fight against corruption that has bedeviled the country by ensuring those culpable are prosecuted.  He pledged that they will ensure the level if corruption is minimized if not fully eradicated. he was speaking in Usenge during the consecration of justice William Ouko as the president of the court of appeal. 